    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Onboard + Provision v2\n\nFront-end POSTs here → checks passcode → **auto-creates the NocoDB leads table** → writes client record → creates + activates wrapper workflow → returns webhook URL + leads_table_id.\n\n### What's new\n- **Auto-creates NocoDB leads table** with all 15 columns (Phone, Name, ConversationID, Stage, Language, Date, Handover, Follow up 1-3, ConvHistory, QualAnswers, BookingTime, LastMsgAt, MemSummary)\n- **No NocoDB fields on the provisioning form** — base URL, token, and table ID are all managed here\n- **qual_questions and bot_config** stored in client record from new wizard fields\n- **leads_table_id returned** in the response for reference\n\n### Set before use\n1. `Set · Settings`: REPLACE_PASSCODE, REPLACE_ENGINE_WORKFLOW_ID, REPLACE_NOCODB_BASE, REPLACE_NOCODB_MASTER_TOKEN, REPLACE_CONTROL_PROJECT, REPLACE_CLIENTS_TABLE, REPLACE_ANALYTICS_TABLE\n2. `NocoDB · Create client`: REPLACE_CONTROL_WORKSPACE / PROJECT / CLIENTS_TABLE + master credential\n3. `HTTP · Create/Activate workflow` + `HTTP · Store workflow id`: Header Auth credential named **n8n API** (X-N8N-API-KEY)\n\n### NocoDB leads table is named\n`Leads_{ClientName}` — created automatically in the project specified by REPLACE_CONTROL_PROJECT.",
        "height": 400, "width": 520
      },
      "id": "note", "name": "README", "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote", "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [ -1100, -140 ]
    }
  ],
